CEREBRA-Q: QUANTUM NEUROMORPHIC SYSTEM FABRIC SUPERCOMPUTER

COMPREHENSIVE ARCHITECTURAL DEEP DIVE

---

1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY & PHILOSOPHICAL FOUNDATION

1.1 The Paradigm Convergence Imperative

Current computing faces three fundamental walls:

· Von Neumann Bottleneck (memory-processor separation)
· Quantum-Classical Interface Friction (coherence time vs. processing speed)
· Energy-Efficiency Plateau (end of Dennard scaling)

Cerebra-Q addresses these through triple-paradigm integration:

1. Quantum Computing: For exponential parallelism in specific problem spaces
2. Neuromorphic Engineering: For energy-efficient, brain-inspired processing
3. Supercomputing Fabric: For massive-scale integration and classical co-processing

1.2 Core Innovation Thesis

"We don't need better quantum computers OR better neuromorphic chips—we need a fundamentally new computational substrate where quantum phenomena and neural dynamics co-evolve on a reconfigurable fabric."

