2. ARCHITECTURAL OVERVIEW: THE 7-LAYER FABRIC

2.1 Physical Layer (Layer 1)

```
PHYSICAL SUBSTRATE COMPOSITION:
├── Quantum Processing Tiles (QPTs)
│   ├── Topological qubit arrays (Majorana zero modes)
│   ├── Photonic quantum buses (entanglement distribution)
│   ├── Superconducting resonator banks (coherent memory)
│   └── Cryo-CMOS control circuitry (4K operation)
├── Neuromorphic Processing Tiles (NPTs)
│   ├── Memristive crossbar arrays (128×128 per tile)
│   ├── Spiking neuron circuits (adaptive threshold)
│   ├── Local plasticity engines (STDP, Hebbian)
│   └── Analog-digital interfaces
└── Classical Processing Tiles (CPTs)
    ├── RISC-V cores with quantum/neuro extensions
    ├── Optical routing controllers
    └── Fabric management processors
```

2.2 Quantum-Neuromorphic Interface Layer (Layer 2)

Quantum State → Spike Conversion (Q2S):

· Coherence-to-Spike Encoder: Maps qubit superposition collapse events to precisely timed spikes
· Entanglement Detector Circuits: Identifies Bell state measurements for correlation-based learning
· Quantum Amplitude Sampling: Converts probability amplitudes to spike rate codes

Spike → Quantum State Conversion (S2Q):

· Temporally-Encoded Qubit Initialization: Spike timing patterns prepare specific quantum states
· Population Coding to Superposition: Multiple neuromorphic cores collectively initialize entangled states

2.3 Fabric Interconnect Layer (Layer 3)

Three-Tier Hybrid Network:

```
TIER 1: INTRA-TILE (Nanosecond, cryogenic)
├── Superconducting nanowire links (10GHz, 0.5pj/bit)
├── Silicon photonic waveguides (8 wavelengths, 100Gbps/lane)
└── Reconfigurable crossbar switches (5ns reconfiguration)

TIER 2: INTER-TILE (Microsecond, mixed-temp)
├── Photonic network-on-chip (256×256 optical routers)
├── Quantum state teleportation channels (entanglement distribution)
├── Spike event routing fabric (address-event representation)
└── Classical packet-switched network (Ethernet-like)

TIER 3: INTER-RACK (Millisecond, room temp)
├── Free-space optical interconnects (Petabit/s per link)
├── Microwave-to-optical converters (quantum state preservation)
└── Hierarchical spike aggregation trees
```

2.4 Memory Coherence Layer (Layer 4)

Unified Address Space:

· Quantum Memory Pages: Coherent states with entanglement metadata
· Synaptic Memory Pages: Analog weight matrices with plasticity rules
· Classical Memory Pages: Standard binary data
· Holographic Associative Memory: Content-addressable across all types

Coherence Protocol (QNeuro-Coherence):

· Tracks quantum entanglement relationships alongside classical cache lines
· Maintains consistency between quantum amplitudes and neuromorphic weight updates
· Implements "eventual consistency" for probabilistic computations

2.5 Execution Layer (Layer 5)

Hybrid Execution Model:

```
QUANTUM EXECUTION CONTEXT:
├── Circuit execution with real-time error correction
├── Variational algorithm optimization loops
├── Quantum annealing schedules
└── Measurement and post-processing pipelines

NEUROMORPHIC EXECUTION CONTEXT:
├── Spiking neural network simulation
├── Online learning with local plasticity
├── Winner-take-all competitions
└── Temporal pattern recognition

HYBRID EXECUTION CONTEXT:
├── Quantum-enhanced neural training
├── Neuromorphic quantum state tomography
├── Quantum-inspired neural architectures
└── Co-evolution of quantum and neural dynamics
```

2.6 Control & Orchestration Layer (Layer 6)

Distributed Resource Manager:

· Dynamically allocates quantum, neuromorphic, and classical resources
· Migrates computations based on coherence time, energy budget, and accuracy requirements
· Implements "graceful degradation" when quantum decoherence occurs

Adaptive Fabric Reconfiguration:

· Repurposes neuromorphic tiles as quantum error correction circuits when needed
· Converts classical tiles into spike routers during high neural activity
· Adjusts clock domains and voltage/frequency scaling per tile

2.7 Application Interface Layer (Layer 7)

Abstract Machine Model:

· Quantum Neural Turing Machine extension
· Probabilistic spiking neural networks with quantum operators
· Unified tensor abstraction spanning quantum states and neural activations

