3. QUANTUM-NEUROMORPHIC SYNTHESIS: DETAILED MECHANISMS

3.1 Quantum Synaptic Processing

Entangled Weight Matrices:

```
Traditional synapse: w_ij (scalar weight)
Quantum synapse: |w_ij⟩ = α|0⟩ + β|1⟩ + γ|+⟩ + δ|-⟩

Where:
|0⟩, |1⟩: Basis weight states
|+⟩, |-⟩: Superposition weight states
α,β,γ,δ: Complex amplitudes representing weight uncertainty
```

Quantum-STDP Learning Rule:

```
Δ|w⟩ = ∫[pre(t) × post(t-τ) × U(τ)] dτ × |η⟩

Where:
pre(t), post(t): Spike functions in superposition
U(τ): Quantum kernel (complex-valued, non-local)
|η⟩: Learning rate in superposition (allows exploration)
```

3.2 Neuromorphic Quantum Error Correction

Brain-Inspired Surface Codes:

· Map topological quantum codes onto neuromorphic crossbars
· Use spike-timing patterns to detect and correct errors
· Implement "neural belief propagation" for decoding

Attention-Based Syndrome Decoding:

· Neuromorphic cores implement attention mechanisms on quantum error syndromes
· Focus computational resources on most probable error locations
· Continuous online learning improves decoding over time

3.3 Quantum-Enhanced Neural Dynamics

Coherent Neural Oscillations:

· Use quantum phase coherence to synchronize distant neural populations
· Implement "quantum binding" for feature integration problems
· Entangle attention mechanisms across sensory modalities

Probabilistic Inference with Quantum Amplitudes:

· Bayesian inference with quantum probability amplitudes
· Sampling from quantum distributions for Monte Carlo methods
· Quantum amplitude estimation for accelerated inference

