5. PROGRAMMING MODEL & SOFTWARE ECOSYSTEM

5.1 Cerebra-Q Instruction Set Architecture (CQ-ISA)

Three-Address Quantum-Neuro Instructions:

```
QNEURO-ADD |ψ⟩, |φ⟩, |θ⟩    # Quantum neural addition
QSPIKE-GEN t, pattern, |ψ⟩   # Generate spikes from quantum state
ENTANGLE-SYNAPSE i, j, k     # Create entangled synaptic connection
MEASURE-LEARN addr, rule     # Measure and apply learning rule
```

Extended Addressing Modes:

· Quantum indirect: |register⟩ contains superposition of addresses
· Spike-time relative: Addresses relative to temporal spike patterns
· Entanglement-based: Access all entangled memory locations simultaneously

5.2 Programming Languages

NeuroQ# (Microsoft extension):

```csharp
operation QuantumNeuralLayer(qubits: Qubit[], spikes: Spike[]) : Double[] {
    // Prepare quantum state from spikes
    PrepareStateFromSpikes(spikes, qubits);
    
    // Apply quantum neural circuit
    within {
        EntangleSynapses(qubits[0..3]);
        ApplyQuantumSTDP(qubits);
    } apply {
        // Neuromorphic processing during coherence
        ProcessSpikesOnQuantumHardware(spikes);
    }
    
    // Measure and return classical results
    return MeasureAndCollapse(qubits);
}
```

PyTorch-QNeuro:

```python
import torch
import torch.qneuro as qn

class QuantumSpikingNN(qn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.quantum_conv = qn.QuantumConv2d(3, 16, kernel_size=3)
        self.spiking_pool = qn.SpikingMaxPool2d(2)
        self.entangled_fc = qn.EntangledLinear(16*14*14, 10)
        
    def forward(self, x):
        # Quantum feature extraction
        x = self.quantum_conv(x)  # Returns quantum state
        # Convert to spikes
        spikes = qn.quantum_to_spikes(x, threshold=0.7)
        # Spatiotemporal processing
        x = self.spiking_pool(spikes)
        # Entangled classification
        return self.entangled_fc(x)
```

5.3 Compiler Infrastructure

Cerebra-Q LLVM Backend:

```
Source → [Frontend] → QNeuro-IR → [Optimizer] → Fabric-Mapped IR → [Scheduler] → Binary
                │           │           │              │
           Quantum      Neuromorphic  Classical   Hybrid optimizations
           passes         passes        passes
```

Key Optimizations:

· Coherence-aware scheduling: Group quantum operations before decoherence
· Energy-latency tradeoff: Choose quantum vs neuromorphic vs classical based on constraints
· Entanglement routing: Minimize communication for entangled computations

5.4 Runtime System

Quantum-Neuro OS (QnOS):

· Microkernel architecture (seL4-based)
· Quantum process: Manages qubit allocation, error correction
· Neuromorphic process: Handles spike routing, plasticity updates
· Fabric manager: Coordinates resource allocation

Virtualization Support:

· Quantum time-sharing: Multiple quantum circuits on same physical qubits
· Neuromorphic multiplexing: Many neural networks on shared crossbars
· Isolation guarantees: Prevent quantum interference between tenants

